{"name": "nomad-dos-fingerprints", "metadata": {"name": "nomad-dos-fingerprints", "version": "1.0.2", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://gitlab.mpcdf.mpg.de/nomad-lab/nomad-dos-fingerprints", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["nomad-lab"], "summary": "An implementation of DOS fingerprints for the NOMAD Laboratory.", "upload_time": 1726070801}, "documentation": ["This package implements fingerprints of the electronic density-of-states (DOS) for the evaluation of similarity of materials based on their electronic structures.\n\nThe fingerprints are based on a modification on the D-Fingerprints presented in Ref. [1].\nOur modification allows to target specific energy ranges for the evaluation of the similarity of the electronic structure.\nAs a similarity measure we use the Tanimoto coefficient [2].\n\n# Usage\n\nFingerprints are instances of the `DOSFingerprint()` class and can be calculated by providing the energy in [Joule] and the DOS in [states/unit cell/Joule] to the `calculate()` method. Furthermore, the parameters of a non-uniform grid can be chosen. The default grid is specialized on the energy range between -10 and 5 eV and emphasizes the upper valence region.\n\n```Python\nfrom nomad_dos_fingerprints import DOSFingerprint\ndos_fingerprint = DOSFingerprint().calculate(<dos_energies>,<dos_values>)\n```\n\nTo evaluate the similarity, the function `tanimoto_similarity()` can be used:\n\n```Python\nfrom nomad_dos_fingerprints import tanimoto_similarity\ntc = tanimoto_similarity(dos_fingerprint_1, dos_fingerprint_2)\n```\n\n# References\n\n[1] Isayev _et al._, Chem. Mater. 2015, 27, 3, 735\u2013743 (doi:10.1021/cm503507h)\n\n[2] P. Willet _et al._, J. Chem. Inf. Comput . 38 , 983 996 (1998) (doi:10.1021/ci9800211)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.similarity", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.similarity.match_fingerprints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fingerprint1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fingerprint2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.similarity.tanimoto_similarity", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fingerprint1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fingerprint2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.DOSFingerprint", "xref": {"fqname": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.DOSfingerprint.DOSFingerprint", "project": null}}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.Grid", "xref": {"fqname": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid.Grid", "project": null}}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.tanimoto_similarity", "xref": {"fqname": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.similarity.tanimoto_similarity", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid.Grid", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid.Grid.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "grid_id", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "grid_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mu", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sigma", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cutoff", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "num_bins", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "original_stepsize", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid.Grid.get_grid_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nomad_dos_fingerprints.grid.Grid.resolve_grid_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "grid_id", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "document